    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-10-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-10-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="339"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d339">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum</hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chinese Legation</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-10-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 26, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cablegram from Viceroy Chang Chih-tung, dated October 25, states that governor of
                    Shensi has reported that Kang Yi died on October 18; that Yu Hsien (late
                    governor of Shansi) has committed suicide by swallowing gold leaf, and Prince
                    Tuan has not been permitted to accompany the court.</p>
                <p>A cablegram dated October 24 from Director-General Sheng states that an Imperial
                    decree has been issued directing Prince Ching and Earl Li to fix and submit for
                    approval the several penalties to be inflicted on those princes and ministers
                    that ought to be punished. He adds that Kang Yi has died of sickness and that
                    Prince Tuan and Prince Chwang have not been allowed to accompany the court to
                    Shensi.</p>
            </div>
